title: Herculean!
author: suprabuilder
pages:
#- -------------------        
       Herculean!

-------------------
By Suprabuilder
For Polynesia
#- There was a nation of Iron and Man, in the Old Land, that is no longer there.

Herculean! Herculean! A land great and wide! The land of the proud and the wise! A Nation of the Great Demise!
#- Herculean was Great and Powerful! Rich and plentiful! United and Strong! Such was the nation of Herculean!

Herculean! Herculean! A land great and wide! The land of the proud and the wise! A Nation of the Great Demise!
#- However, to the West, the land of the 48 Mayors looked in envy! 

Herculean! Herculean! We 48 are Irate! We wish for Unity among eachother, but are divided by Hate!
#- And to the North, the Emperor of the Island looked in envy!

Herculean! Herculean! How great is thee! For you are the one more powerful than me!
#- Alas, to the East, The Red Tyranny looked in envy! 

Herculean! Herculean! So many people, so little riches! Your greatness makes me malicious! 
#- The Nation of Herculean sat content at the top. But as day comes to night, greatness will fall!

Herculean! Herculean! Evil is on the way, much to your dismay!
#- From the South came the Troublesome Merchant! Such was the Merchant, his evil ways collapsed nations!

Herculean! Herculean! Evil is on the way! Turn it away!
#- Herculean rejected the merchant, and sent him away, much to the Merchant's rage!

Herculean! Herculean! does trouble end yet? Is there still a threat? 

#- The Merchant went to work! Herculean would pay! 

"One of our mayors was killed!" Said the West,
"Some of my land was taken!" Said the North,
"Who destroyed this town of mine!" Said the East

#- All three looked to the merchant, the trouble maker,

"Was it you?" They asked 
"NO!" Said the merchant, "It was Herculean!"

#- In their anger, The three nations invaded Herculean! Little did they know, the Merchant framed Herculean!

Herculean! Herculean! By the Merchant you were named! You've been framed!
#- Herculean fought hard, but was crushed from all sides! 

Herculean! Herculean! From you we have recieved Power! Unity! Greatness! Now you will have none! 
#- The nations left Herculean with all they envied before, and the merchant continued his evil.

Herculean! Herculean! Come back to me! Take back your power and bring justice to the world!

#-         The End
#- 